{
  "texts": [
    "The segmentation results of stuff and things are distinguished by different colors (Elharrouss et al. 2021).",
    "Comparatively, to semantic and instance segmentation, panoptic segmentation examines each component of the entire scene globally, significantly improving the ability to perceive the scene, making it a suitable tool for automating driving, video surveillance, and analyzing medical images.",
    "Due to the perceived defects in both semantic segmentation and instance segmentation, early panoptic segmentation algorithms are direct combinations of the semantic segmentation model and the instance segmentation model.",
    "Mask R-CNN is the most used method for panoptic segmentation (Li and Chen 2022).",
    "The UPSNet (Lei et al. 2023; Mao et al. 2023), FPSNet (Nie et al. 2023; Simeth et al. 2023), and VPSNet (Gopinath et al. 2023; Choudhuri et al. 2023) are some of its backbone architectures."
  ]
}